##What are these people waiting for at 4:00 in the morning

Southreviews

Functional presentation, the power of calm

Each in his own way
For Wuhan and for myself

At four o'clock in the morning, people in the depths of their dreamland wonder what kind of scene it would be like to be in Wuhan at this time and at the Concord Hospital at this time.

As of February 19, Wuhan Union Hospital had treated 1,055 patients with NCP, of whom 98.2% were in severe or critical condition. Here, Guangdong chi-aid Hubei Medical Team members and Hubei Local medical staff fought side by side, day and night and death struggle for life.

From southern China, another "hero city" of the retrograde, "foreign" as "my hometown" , spent a memorable "four o'clock in the morning.

In the early hours of the morning, members of the medical team from National Sun Yat-sen University Sun Yat-sen Memorial Hospital, braving the cold wind from Jiangcheng, set out from their station to the Union hospital. The streets of Wuhan are empty and lonely, and I'm afraid they're the only ones who see it every day.

The back of a medic at National Sun Yat-sen University Sun Yat-sen Memorial Hospital

"people ask me if I'm nervous, but I don't have time to be nervous, " said Dr. Wang Juan, a National Sun Yat-sen University oncologist.

"If there's one thing I'd like to do right now, it's to take off my mask, breathe in the natural air and walk around the streets of Wuhan with my colleagues, " said Zhao Yingying, a nurse at Guangdong No. 2 Hospital of Traditional Chinese medicine in the quarantine zone, because there was no nurse in the quarantine area, she worked three jobs, helping patients with their daily treatments, as well as fetching water, delivering food, cleaning the ward and comforting them. "I'm tired, but I feel a sense of accomplishment when I see my patients recover. ".

4:00 in the morning

On February 20,101 members of the 21st batch of medical aid team from Guangdong Province left for Hubei. As of that day, Guangdong chi-aid Hubei Medical Team 2249 people.

Guangzhou is also a "late night" city. Chen Yan, who grew up and worked here, is an ordinary office worker in a public institution. She had never imagined that she would be so closely associated with the 2,000-strong front line of "white soldiers. ". Her unit, the Guangdong Provincial Youth League committee, and the front-line medical team set up wechat groups one by one according to hospitals and so on. She is the "leader of the group" , responsible for keeping the group, registering every need of the front-line personnel, and providing feedback to solve the results. "The front-line medics are so pressed for time, they send a message, and I usually reply in seconds. That way they can rest assured that they are doing something else. "

"The provincial epidemic prevention and Control Headquarters has people on the front line to do support work, but they certainly can't take care of more than 2,000 people. So we will build clusters one by one to contact directly, respond quickly and do our best to help the medical staff to solve some of the inconveniences and distract them less,"said the head of Chen's unit. "The demands vary from medical supplies to waterproof shoes and emergency pants, " Chen said. "I will show my colleagues a yellow card if it is not completely resolved by the third day. ".

01
At this moment, we are all "the Guardians. "

In the impression of Volunteer Yu Sha, Wuhan is not a snowy city, usually only once or twice a winter, and the snow is often very small, can not pile up, quickly melted. On February 15, it snowed heavily in Wuhan. The next day, before going out, she found a thick down jacket, hid her face behind her mask and collar, tightened her hat, and went out with a shiver, "so cold. " Every time she took a deep breath, her glasses were covered with a thin layer of heat.

"We need five volunteers with driving license and skilled driving skills to deliver the vehicle to the Phoenix Hotel in country garden, Hannan, where a Guangdong medical team is stationed. " As soon as the wechat group broke the news, she signed up to undertake the task.

"We didn't get off work on time, the hospital was far from the station, and if we couldn't catch the bus, we would have to wait an hour and a half or even four hours, " said Qiu Yihong, the head of the Hubei Medical Team at National Sun Yat-sen University Sun Yat-sen Memorial Hospital, on Wechat, "really greatly affected the rest. " The medical team to and from the hospital and the station, most or to take a regular shuttle bus system, medical staff more inconvenience.

Chen Yan immediately told this matter and the unit. After some twists and turns, the unit and a car rental platform agreed to mobilize the platform's local vehicle resources in Wuhan to set up an emergency vehicle fleet, implement vehicle scheduling arrangements according to the needs of various medical teams, and ensure convenient transportation for medical team members. As of February 21, demand for 25 vehicles had been met.

As a result of the outbreak control, from the car rental platform of the store to take the car, and then sent to the hotel where the medical team has become a problem. Yusha and the other volunteers' roles are as vehicle "porters" . On Feb. 15, five commercial vehicles were waiting to be moved, according to Wechat Group.

WECHAT group has become a small bridge connecting Guangdong and Hubei. Guangdong Provincial Party Committee of the Youth League initiated "youth as a tribute to the white-clothed soldiers" , and quickly built 35"support front-line medical staff" wechat docking group with Guangdong chi-yuan medical team in Hubei. Front-line personnel in need, but not through the Front Command coordination, will be in the group "help. ".

"every time I 'eliminate' a need, I will paste a small flower on my notebook, " Chen said, opening a notebook filled with small flowers. "there are some problems, and we have to rely on the local Youth League committee and volunteers to help us. " On Chen's mobile phone, the wechat group was also "born" alongside the medical team, as well as communication groups with Hubei and Wuhan Brother Units and volunteers.

"wechat groups don't discuss and post topics that are not related to support work. Don't brush groups. . Don't add wechat to front-line medical personnel unless necessary. . " Chen's colleagues even drafted "guidelines for supporting front-line medical personnel in wechat groups. " There are clear rules about who should be in the group and what roles should be played. "We worked with the Hubei authorities, and the needs of the medical team were basically solved within two days. Volunteers from the two provinces helped us with a lot of things. "

On Feb. 16, volunteers in Wuhan decided to leave at 10 a.m. in order to get the bus there earlier than planned, when it was supposed to leave at 1 p.m.

More than 10:00 arrived at the rental platform of the Wangjiawan store, two cars because more than a month unused, serious lack of electricity, charging half an hour after no reaction. Considering that the same problem might exist with Dunkou's two cars, the volunteers split up, with two going to Dunkou and three staying in Wangjiawan.

After two hours of recharging, the car was fully powered up just after 12 noon. The volunteers did not have time to eat, immediately drove to Hannan, around 1 o'clock to the car to the National Sun Yat-sen University First Hospital medical team stationed.

After picking up their cars from the car rental platform, the volunteers took five cars to the medical team's station

There are plenty of willing volunteers, and sometimes even have to "Rob" to get the job. Special period, they have also become "guard the crowd" , not on the way to complete the task, is waiting to guard the WECHAT group assigned volunteer service task. As soon as the recruit's released, it'll be full in no time.

I don't want to rest, I want to do more. Feng Yan was one of the volunteers recruited by the Hanyang District Youth League committee in Wuhan and also took part in the task of delivering vehicles to the Guangdong medical team. These days she never stops delivering and distributing supplies. After becoming a volunteer, she saw a lot of touching and sad. And the front lines are tense, efficient, and filled with hope.

The gloves were worn for less than an hour, and Feng Yan could already feel her hands sweating profusely because they were not breathable. But she, who travels to and from the front, observes that the gloves of the front line medical staff are mostly left on. "It must be very uncomfortable. " On Feb. 14, Feng finished a busy day and sent out a message to her friends. "The most Special Valentine's Day of her life. "

02
"If you need anything else, I'll call you. "

I'll go to the mall and ask for some more supplies. Then I'll contact the people at the wholesale market. We have a lever in our warehouse that can hang clothes for the medical staff. These days, she is just as busy as the volunteer Feng Yan.

On February 14, the weather forecast for Hubei was that temperatures would plummet and snow would fall in many places. The Guangdong medical team did not prepare enough warm supplies. A knitting enterprise in Foshan, Guangdong, donated 1,125 sets of down jackets through the local Youth League committee for medical and health care workers in Guangdong and Hubei. On the 16th and 17th, the cold yellow warning issued by the Foshan Meteorological Observatory was upgraded to an orange alert, there are still 12 volunteers in the Minute to Win It, according to the gender of the medical team members, yards, sorted out more than 1,000 pieces of down jackets sent to Wuhan Emergency. Tan Yanling, a volunteer with the Foshan Youth Volunteer commando team, said, "we are on standby. The Communist Youth League and Municipal Party Committee has sent out a recruitment call. We will act immediately. We only hope that the down jacket can be quickly put into the hands of the medical team. "

Volunteers in Foshan sorted down jackets according to hospital demand and size

More than 1,000 pieces of down garments were sent to Wuhan by car

In view of the possible road conditions after the snowfall, also coordinated multiple parties to buy a batch of boots and insoles to the medical team. "It's very cold in Wuhan today, with sleet and sleet, " said the captain of the Second Medical Aid Hubei medical team of Guangdong Province. "But I received a down jacket from Guangdong. My heart is warm. "

"We also need ordinary long-sleeve rain boots for work, size 41-2, size 42-5, size 43-2, size 44-1, " said a request from the frontline medical team on the wechat group. "Is there a quick way to buy a laptop and printer? For Urgent Office use. " "We need A4 CARTON! " "Can you supply us with 63 clothes hangers? " "Do you have waterproof sweatpants? " ..

The medical team received long-barreled boots and cotton insoles

The Hubei Front Line needs many of these small but indispensable needs. "The laptops and printers needed by the first Zhongshan Hospital have been coordinated and purchased, and they will be sent directly to the medical team tomorrow afternoon, " said Wang Bo, a receiver for the Municipal Party Committee of Wuhan, who spoke late at night on Wechat.

Supplies such as computers and printers have been sent to the medical team

"to the medical team of things, I will send as soon as possible, the price will be much lower" , Mu Mu said on wechat. Learn that the front-line medical staff need waterproof pants, but from Guangdong to buy re-mail is very inconvenient, Chen Yan's partner Li Ying is on the Internet to find the local shop in Wuhan Mu. The warm bath is prepared for the front-line medical team, without a word to make a minimum price, drive delivery to the hands of medical staff, and proposed to send thick leggings, socks, and so on, even the doctor travel needs, she also make arrangements to help.

"actually, we don't know how much we can help. But if I can do a little thing, I feel in my heart that I am worthy of Wuhan and the people who have come all the way to Wuhan to help. " Xiong Youming, the volunteer leader, said, keep a journal of your daily activities.

Don't ask where you come from, only where you come from. "He's been sleeping for a long time, " they believe. "He'll wake up soon. "

03
"When I came to Wuhan, I found peace like never before. "

"To come to Wuhan, I have never had the calm, very happy. I do not know why, a little fear means no, I admire myself. ". Zhang posted the message at 11:30 p.m. on Feb. 18 as he was driving from Guangdong to Wuhan for support.

Known as "Tiger Brother, " Zhang Kai is a former soldier and former police officer who now lives in Hongmei, Guangdong, Guangdong Province, and is the "backbone" of Hong Mei's volunteer caring motorcade. During the Spring Festival, he and his car friends in Dongguan every day pick up and send medical staff, emergency personnel, vehicles..

Zhang Kai picks up medical staff in Dongguan during the Spring Festival

Zhang Kai's trip to Wuhan was not easy. He repeatedly applied to the Guangdong Volunteer Action Guidance Center to go to Wuhan as a volunteer, Take Guangdong to Wuhan medical staff to and from work. But the Center for the safety of volunteers, he has not agreed to go, it has not helped him communicate the procedures to Wuhan.

So, Zhang Kai contacted a local friend in Wuhan, actually got a pass, and drove off. But his teammates did not have his luck, drive to Wuhan, incomplete procedures can not get in, and turned back to Guangdong. Now, Zhang Kai and local car friends together, specifically for the hospital delivery of supplies. In his spare time, he will pick up and drop off people in need in Wuhan.

Zhang Kai also has many "colleagues" in Wuhan. Wuhan empty streets, can still see a variety of private cars passing, the formation of the epidemic in the civil volunteer convoy. Like Wuhan's "capillary" , these convoys transport supplies to where they are needed, sometimes in protective clothing, goggles, sometimes in suction machines, oxygen tanks, sometimes in vegetables and milk. Between them, also rely on one another wechat group connection.

As far as Guangzhou, 980 kilometers away, Chen Yan has been "guarding the group, " one by one to note the need, and one by one feedback, whether late at night or during the day.

At the same time, Guangdong, Hubei and various groups of volunteers, and issued a new task, there will be new volunteers to "single. ". Dr. Wang Juan, of the National Sun Yat-sen University, was busy in the ICU. Also busy, there are countless in the transport station, community bayonet, factory floor... people.

In Guangdong alone, as of February 21,61,203 volunteers and 94,042 registered with the "I volunteer" system for voluntary service in epidemic prevention and control, "there are a lot of projects that haven't been released in time to go straight to work. "

At this moment, we are all "the Guardians. "

In the impression of Volunteer Yu Sha, Wuhan is not a snowy city, usually only once or twice a winter, and the snow is often very small, can not pile up, quickly melted. On February 15, it snowed heavily in Wuhan. The next day, before going out, she found a thick down jacket, hid her face behind her mask and collar, tightened her hat, and went out with a shiver, "so cold. " Every time she took a deep breath, her glasses were covered with a thin layer of heat.

"We need five volunteers with driving license and skilled driving skills to deliver the vehicle to the Phoenix Hotel in country garden, Hannan, where a Guangdong medical team is stationed. " As soon as the wechat group broke the news, she signed up to undertake the task.

"We didn't get off work on time, the hospital was far from the station, and if we couldn't catch the bus, we would have to wait an hour and a half or even four hours, " said Qiu Yihong, the head of the Hubei Medical Team at National Sun Yat-sen University Sun Yat-sen Memorial Hospital, on Wechat, "really greatly affected the rest. " The medical team to and from the hospital and the station, most or to take a regular shuttle bus system, medical staff more inconvenience.

Chen Yan immediately told this matter and the unit. After some twists and turns, the unit and a car rental platform agreed to mobilize the platform's local vehicle resources in Wuhan to set up an emergency vehicle fleet, implement vehicle scheduling arrangements according to the needs of various medical teams, and ensure convenient transportation for medical team members. As of February 21, demand for 25 vehicles had been met.

As a result of the outbreak control, from the car rental platform of the store to take the car, and then sent to the hotel where the medical team has become a problem. Yusha and the other volunteers' roles are as vehicle "porters" . On Feb. 15, five commercial vehicles were waiting to be moved, according to Wechat Group.

WECHAT group has become a small bridge connecting Guangdong and Hubei. Guangdong Provincial Party Committee of the Youth League initiated "youth as a tribute to the white-clothed soldiers" , and quickly built 35"support front-line medical staff" wechat docking group with Guangdong chi-yuan medical team in Hubei. Front-line personnel in need, but not through the Front Command coordination, will be in the group "help. ".

"every time I 'eliminate' a need, I will paste a small flower on my notebook, " Chen said, opening a notebook filled with small flowers. "there are some problems, and we have to rely on the local Youth League committee and volunteers to help us. " On Chen's mobile phone, the wechat group was also "born" alongside the medical team, as well as communication groups with Hubei and Wuhan Brother Units and volunteers.

"wechat groups don't discuss and post topics that are not related to support work. Don't brush groups. . Don't add wechat to front-line medical personnel unless necessary. . " Chen's colleagues even drafted "guidelines for supporting front-line medical personnel in wechat groups. " There are clear rules about who should be in the group and what roles should be played. "We worked with the Hubei authorities, and the needs of the medical team were basically solved within two days. Volunteers from the two provinces helped us with a lot of things. "

On Feb. 16, volunteers in Wuhan decided to leave at 10 a.m. in order to get the bus there earlier than planned, when it was supposed to leave at 1 p.m.

More than 10:00 arrived at the rental platform of the Wangjiawan store, two cars because more than a month unused, serious lack of electricity, charging half an hour after no reaction. Considering that the same problem might exist with Dunkou's two cars, the volunteers split up, with two going to Dunkou and three staying in Wangjiawan.

After two hours of recharging, the car was fully powered up just after 12 noon. The volunteers did not have time to eat, immediately drove to Hannan, around 1 o'clock to the car to the National Sun Yat-sen University First Hospital medical team stationed.

After picking up their cars from the car rental platform, the volunteers took five cars to the medical team's station

There are plenty of willing volunteers, and sometimes even have to "Rob" to get the job. Special period, they have also become "guard the crowd" , not on the way to complete the task, is waiting to guard the WECHAT group assigned volunteer service task. As soon as the recruit's released, it'll be full in no time.

I don't want to rest, I want to do more. Feng Yan was one of the volunteers recruited by the Hanyang District Youth League committee in Wuhan and also took part in the task of delivering vehicles to the Guangdong medical team. These days she never stops delivering and distributing supplies. After becoming a volunteer, she saw a lot of touching and sad. And the front lines are tense, efficient, and filled with hope.

The gloves were worn for less than an hour, and Feng Yan could already feel her hands sweating profusely because they were not breathable. But she, who travels to and from the front, observes that the gloves of the front line medical staff are mostly left on. "It must be very uncomfortable. " On Feb. 14, Feng finished a busy day and sent out a message to her friends. "The most Special Valentine's Day of her life. "

02
"If you need anything else, I'll call you. "

02

"If you need anything else, I'll call you. "

I'll go to the mall and ask for some more supplies. Then I'll contact the people at the wholesale market. We have a lever in our warehouse that can hang clothes for the medical staff. These days, she is just as busy as the volunteer Feng Yan.

On February 14, the weather forecast for Hubei was that temperatures would plummet and snow would fall in many places. The Guangdong medical team did not prepare enough warm supplies. A knitting enterprise in Foshan, Guangdong, donated 1,125 sets of down jackets through the local Youth League committee for medical and health care workers in Guangdong and Hubei. On the 16th and 17th, the cold yellow warning issued by the Foshan Meteorological Observatory was upgraded to an orange alert, there are still 12 volunteers in the Minute to Win It, according to the gender of the medical team members, yards, sorted out more than 1,000 pieces of down jackets sent to Wuhan Emergency. Tan Yanling, a volunteer with the Foshan Youth Volunteer commando team, said, "we are on standby. The Communist Youth League and Municipal Party Committee has sent out a recruitment call. We will act immediately. We only hope that the down jacket can be quickly put into the hands of the medical team. "

Volunteers in Foshan sorted down jackets according to hospital demand and size

More than 1,000 pieces of down garments were sent to Wuhan by car

In view of the possible road conditions after the snowfall, also coordinated multiple parties to buy a batch of boots and insoles to the medical team. "It's very cold in Wuhan today, with sleet and sleet, " said the captain of the Second Medical Aid Hubei medical team of Guangdong Province. "But I received a down jacket from Guangdong. My heart is warm. "

"We also need ordinary long-sleeve rain boots for work, size 41-2, size 42-5, size 43-2, size 44-1, " said a request from the frontline medical team on the wechat group. "Is there a quick way to buy a laptop and printer? For Urgent Office use. " "We need A4 CARTON! " "Can you supply us with 63 clothes hangers? " "Do you have waterproof sweatpants? " ..

The medical team received long-barreled boots and cotton insoles

The Hubei Front Line needs many of these small but indispensable needs. "The laptops and printers needed by the first Zhongshan Hospital have been coordinated and purchased, and they will be sent directly to the medical team tomorrow afternoon, " said Wang Bo, a receiver for the Municipal Party Committee of Wuhan, who spoke late at night on Wechat.

Supplies such as computers and printers have been sent to the medical team

"to the medical team of things, I will send as soon as possible, the price will be much lower" , Mu Mu said on wechat. Learn that the front-line medical staff need waterproof pants, but from Guangdong to buy re-mail is very inconvenient, Chen Yan's partner Li Ying is on the Internet to find the local shop in Wuhan Mu. The warm bath is prepared for the front-line medical team, without a word to make a minimum price, drive delivery to the hands of medical staff, and proposed to send thick leggings, socks, and so on, even the doctor travel needs, she also make arrangements to help.

"actually, we don't know how much we can help. But if I can do a little thing, I feel in my heart that I am worthy of Wuhan and the people who have come all the way to Wuhan to help. " Xiong Youming, the volunteer leader, said, keep a journal of your daily activities.

Don't ask where you come from, only where you come from. "He's been sleeping for a long time, " they believe. "He'll wake up soon. "

03
"When I came to Wuhan, I found peace like never before. "

03

"When I came to Wuhan, I found peace like never before. "

"To come to Wuhan, I have never had the calm, very happy. I do not know why, a little fear means no, I admire myself. ". Zhang posted the message at 11:30 p.m. on Feb. 18 as he was driving from Guangdong to Wuhan for support.

Known as "Tiger Brother, " Zhang Kai is a former soldier and former police officer who now lives in Hongmei, Guangdong, Guangdong Province, and is the "backbone" of Hong Mei's volunteer caring motorcade. During the Spring Festival, he and his car friends in Dongguan every day pick up and send medical staff, emergency personnel, vehicles..

Zhang Kai picks up medical staff in Dongguan during the Spring Festival

Zhang Kai's trip to Wuhan was not easy. He repeatedly applied to the Guangdong Volunteer Action Guidance Center to go to Wuhan as a volunteer, Take Guangdong to Wuhan medical staff to and from work. But the Center for the safety of volunteers, he has not agreed to go, it has not helped him communicate the procedures to Wuhan.

So, Zhang Kai contacted a local friend in Wuhan, actually got a pass, and drove off. But his teammates did not have his luck, drive to Wuhan, incomplete procedures can not get in, and turned back to Guangdong. Now, Zhang Kai and local car friends together, specifically for the hospital delivery of supplies. In his spare time, he will pick up and drop off people in need in Wuhan.

Zhang Kai also has many "colleagues" in Wuhan. Wuhan empty streets, can still see a variety of private cars passing, the formation of the epidemic in the civil volunteer convoy. Like Wuhan's "capillary" , these convoys transport supplies to where they are needed, sometimes in protective clothing, goggles, sometimes in suction machines, oxygen tanks, sometimes in vegetables and milk. Between them, also rely on one another wechat group connection.

As far as Guangzhou, 980 kilometers away, Chen Yan has been "guarding the group, " one by one to note the need, and one by one feedback, whether late at night or during the day.

At the same time, Guangdong, Hubei and various groups of volunteers, and issued a new task, there will be new volunteers to "single. ". Dr. Wang Juan, of the National Sun Yat-sen University, was busy in the ICU. Also busy, there are countless in the transport station, community bayonet, factory floor... people.

In Guangdong alone, as of February 21,61,203 volunteers and 94,042 registered with the "I volunteer" system for voluntary service in epidemic prevention and control, "there are a lot of projects that haven't been released in time to go straight to work. "

Each in his own way. For Wuhan and for myself.

February 21,2020,10:00 p.m

Written by Yang Shu and Li Ailin
